added.title: Huggbees
added.description: The Brain teams up with The Lobe, so the Titans enlist the help of Freakazoid to stop them.

added.title: Baby Mouth
added.description: In order to find out about his family history, Robin takes a DNA test and discovers he's from Babylon.

added.title: The Cast
added.description: After breaking his leg, Robin is confined to his room and spies through a telescope.

added.title: Superhero Feud
added.description: Control Freak pits the Titans against the DC Superhero Girls to determine who is the best team in the universe.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Dance Crew Edition Part 1
added.description: It's time for another Justice League talent competition and Vibe is joining the judges' panel to critique the moves of the DC universe dance crews.

added.title: The Laziest
added.description: Gumball and Darwin challenge Dad to a "lazy-off."

added.title: The Menu
added.description: The prize jewel on the Secret Joyful Burger menu is a mysterious burger, but to order it you need to know its name. When Larry refuses to tell them what it's called, they go to super-sized lengths to discover it.

added.title: The Heist
added.description: Richard discovers going into a bank whilst wearing a motorcycle helmet can land you in a lot of trouble.

added.title: The Deal
added.description: When Mom wins Employee of the Month at the Rainbow factory, Richard feels like he is never celebrated for all the work he does at home. Nicole is suspicious of how much he actually does, but when Richard goes on strike, his important role in keeping things under control becomes painfully clear...

added.title: The Choices
added.description: When a typically stressful Watterson family dinner pushes her to the edge of her sanity, Nicole starts reminiscing about the time she met Richard. Might her life have been better if she'd never stopped to talk to her future husband and taken a different path instead?

added.title: The Road
added.description:
This episode takes place when the Bears are young cubs! The three bears, on their way through the desert, come upon a giant warehouse. It's like an Amazon fulfillment
center. The Bears try to make this box-filled paradise their home.

added.title: Tote Life
added.description: When a hipster grocery store clerk shames the Bears for asking for plastic grocery bags, the Bears realize that eco-friendly tote bags are their way of gaining acceptance amongst the progressive people of the Bay Area. But in their effort to gain popularity, the Bears let the culture of tote bags take over their lives.

added.title: Video Date
added.description: Panda is an avid e-dater, and when a lovely French woman matches with him and agrees to a video chat date. Panda and his brothers engineer the situation so Panda is able to show the best side of himself on the video chat, even if that side of him is completely exaggerated.

added.title: Chloe and Ice Bear
added.description: On a day out with just Ice Bear, Chloe realizes Ice Bear only runs errands for his brothers. Determined to show him a fun day in the city, Chloe promises to help Ice Bear have a good time, even if it means staying  in a museum after it closes.

added.title: Hibernation
added.description: The bears, being an urban bunch, hadn't ever heard of the idea of hibernation until Chloe tells them about it. Grizz, loving the idea of eating a ton and then just sleeping to his heart's content, goes for it with reckless abandon.  But Grizz is so excited for hibernating... that he can't fall asleep.

added.title: The Eater
added.description: It's Halloween and Apple's not feeling quite right. He takes Onion into the dark depths to find out why.

added.title: Slobbery
added.description: Burger's roommate is not only a problem for him, but for Apple and Onion who need Burger's help for something else.

added.title: Microwave's Dance Club
added.description: DJ Saltfish and MC Ackee are in town for two nights only and Apple and Onion are determined to make the most of it and bust some moves on the dance floor.

added.title: All Work and No Play
added.description: Having finally saved up and aquired an expensive toy race track, Apple and Onion are faced with one problem- there is no time to play with it.

added.title: Drone Shoes
added.description: Can there exist such a thing as drone shoes? It sounds like they would need a huge power capacity.

added.title: Recipe for Disaster
added.description: During Chefapalooza in the Rocky Mountains, three famous chefs and infamous bad-guys, The Tri-Chefta, hunt down Wildvine in hopes of creating their most exotic dish to date.

added.title: Rustbucket RIP
added.description: During a tour of historic Oldeville Ben finds a rare Sumo Slammers card, but when Billy Billions comes to claim the same card Ben has to battle Billy's high-tech drones which have hijacked the Rust Bucket!

added.title: Freaky Gwen Ben
added.description: When Ben interferes with malicious magician Hex's quest for the earth-moving Titan Gloves at a swap meet, he inadvertently switches bodies with Gwen forcing him to walk a mile in her shoes and vice-versa!

added.title: Ben 24hrs
added.description: When Ben (and Gwen!) attempt to stay up all night for Adrenaland, the only theme park open 24/7, he not only fails to utilize his alien powers to stay awake, but his "sleep-alien-ing" causes disaster after disaster that Gwen must fix before things get way out of hand.

added.title: Bright Lights, Black Hearts
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max stop by the graveyard set of Gwen's favorite TV show, The Unalivers, but when Ben discovers its lead, Michael Morningstar, is an energy vampire he goes alien to show the world the real star of the show: Heatblast.

added.title: Stakes Part 1: Marceline the Vampire Queen
added.description: Finn & Jake hunt for a shadowy predator and Marceline asks Princess Bubblegum for a huge favor.

added.title: Stakes Part 2: Everything Stays
added.description: As the sun rises on her last day, Marceline recalls her long extraordinary life.

added.title: Stakes Part 3: Vamps About
added.description: Five foes from Marceline's past come back to cause trouble for the Land of Ooo.

added.title: Stakes Part 4: Empress Eyes
added.description: When one of her oldest adversaries targets the Ice Kingdom, Marceline rushes to Simon's rescue.

added.title: Stakes Part 5: May I Come In?
added.description: Finn, Jake, Marceline, and PB set out to hunt down the Vamps. But who is hunting them?

added.title: Man of the House
added.description: Clarence's first night home alone spirals out of control, forcing Clarence and his pals to wage war against their own home security measures.

added.title: Neighborhood Grill
added.description: Clarence is so troubled by the sight of his teacher in a social setting outside of school, he can't stop himself from intruding on her doomed blind date.

added.title: Ren Faire
added.description: Clarence and his pals venture to the Aberdale Renaissance Faire. Clarence confuses a medieval play for reality, and vows to stop the evil black knight from getting the princess.

added.title: Time Crimes
added.description: When Clarence is convinced he has the power to manipulate time he vows to only use his abilities for good. However, a day at school puts his morals to the test when he's given the ultimate choice to help his friends or pause time in the name of fun.

added.title: Saturday School
added.description: After creating an unapproved mural on a wall at Aberdale Elementary, Clarence, Jeff and Sumo are forced to come to school on a Saturday to clean up as punishment.

added.title: Scary Tales 2
added.description: It's Halloween again and the gang is desperately trying to tell the scariest story to a couple of trick or treaters. Each of the characters takes turns adding onto the last story, going through a haunted glove to a haunted action figure to haunted everything, and even a spooky song! None work in scaring the kids when suddenly a full scale alien invasion happens right before their eyes! Still, the trick or treaters are unimpressed until Richard takes the story stage and delivers a story no kid wants to hear- instead of candy, the trick or treaters would get granola bars! The kids, and Puppycorn, run away screaming.

added.title: Old Lady Bodyguard
added.description: After being "bought" at a charity auction, Hawkodile is forced to spend the day as Old Lady Edith's personal bodyguard.

added.title: Guardian of the Unikingdom
added.description: Hawkodile insists the Unikingdom is more dangerous than it looks and sets out to prove it by taking his friends on bodyguard patrol.

added.title: P.L.O.T. Device 2: Beyond the Bored Dome
added.description: Dr. Fox reprograms the P.L.O.T. Device to only generate boring events, but the gang can't help but add drama and excitement to every scenario.

added.title: Last One There
added.description: When Unikitty accidentally invokes an ancient curse, the gang must beat Master Frown and Brock back to the castle before one of them literally turns into a rotten egg.

added.title: Big Tick
added.description: A giant alien tick that sucks planets dry, lands on Earth with the sole purpose of destroying the planet and only a new alien hero can stop it.

added.title: Grudge Match
added.description: Ben and Kevin 11 are beamed up to a space ship where must learn to battle together in order to bring down a vicious alien fight promoter.

added.title: Secrets
added.description: Grandpa Max's mysterious past comes to light when Vilgax shows up on earth in search of the Omnitrix. And the family must work together to defeat him.

added.title: Evil's Encore
added.description: Dr. Animo reminisces about when he once took control of the Plumber's HQ in Mount Rushmore. (Flashback episode.)

added.title: Return to Forever
added.description: The Forever Knights threaten to use a sinister weapon to erase all alien DNA on Earth unless Ben and Rook can stop them.

added.title: OTTO Motive
added.description: Kevin and Rook run into an old enemy from the Null Void while attending an intergalactic auto show. (Re-introducing classic Ben alien, Upgrade.)

added.title: A Fistful of Brains
added.description: Grandpa Max and Rook are looking all over the galaxy for Ben, who is trapped on Khyber's hidden personal hunting preserve.

added.title: Mystery, Incorporeal
added.description: An old enemy emerges while Ben and Rook visit Kevin and Gwen at college.

added.title: Late Night Good Morning With Uncle Grandpa
added.description: It's the Late Night Good Morning show with your host, Uncle Grandpa!

added.title: MacGuffin
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and a kid embark on a dangerous jungle adventure in search of a legendary MacGuffin.

added.title: Pony Tale
added.description: Uncle Grandpa grows a ponytail, which gains him the attention of a magical pony.

added.title: Older
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa mistakenly transforms a young boy into a three-hundred-year-old man, he must manage to turn the kid back to normal before anyone gets hurt.

added.title: Pal.0
added.description: When the RV's talking computer system malfunctions, Uncle Grandpa and the gang must figure out a way to stop the rogue computer and restore life in the RV back to normal.

added.title: Receta Del Desastre
added.description: Durante el festival gastronómico Chefapalooza en las Montañas Rocosas, el Tri-Chefta, compuesto por tres cocineros famosos y villanos infames, persigue a Wildvine con la esperanza de crear el plato más exótico que jamás hayan preparado.

added.title: Descanse En Paz Rustbucket
added.description: Durante un tour por la histórica ciudad de Oldeville, Ben encuentra una carta de Sumo Slammers poco común. Pero cuando Billy Billones reclama esa carta, Ben debe luchar contra los drones tecnológicos de Billy, ique secuestraron la Chatarra!

added.title: Gwen O Ben
added.description: Cuando Ben interfiere con la misión de Hex -el mago malicioso- para los Titan Gloves, que hacen tareas de movimiento de tierra en un centro de trueque, Hex intercambia el cuerpo de Ben con el de Gwen, lo cual lo obliga a caminar un kilómetro y medio en sus zapatos iy viceversa!

added.title: Ben 24 Horas
added.description: Cuando Ben (iy Gwen!) intenta quedarse despierto toda la noche para ir a Adrenaland -el único parque temático abierto las 24 horas, los siete días de la semana- no solo es incapaz de utilizar sus poderes alienígenas para lograr su objetivo, sino que además su estado de adormecimiento alienígena provoca un desastre tras otro, y Gwen debe arreglar las cosas antes de que todo se salga de control.

added.title: Luces Brillantes, Corazones Oscuros
added.description: Ben, Gwen y Max hacen una parada en el cementerio falso en el que se filma el programa de televisión favorito de Gwen, pero cuando Ben descubre que su protagonista, Michael Morningstar, es un vampiro de la energía, se transforma en alienígena para mostrarle al mundo quién es la verdadera estrella del programa: Fuego.

removed.title: The Diet
removed.description: Gumball and Darwin discover the reason Dad's diet wasn't working was that he was actually on ten diets and eating a meal for each of them. They eventually manage to help him lose weight, but Richard's newfound buffness also brings out his more obnoxious side.

removed.title: Falafel's in Jail
removed.description: Falafel's in trouble with the law despite pleading his innocence. Apple and Onion vow to break him out.

removed.title: Burrito
removed.description: A Pardo le gustan los burritos. Mucho. Tanto que cuando un restaurant elabora un Burrito tamaño oso, Pardo se obliga a comer semejante obra de arte majestuosa. Lleva el burrito consigo a todas partes y lo convierte en una parte nueva y cada vez más olorosa de su vida.

removed.title: Hoyo En 10
removed.description: Mientras Ben juega al minigolf, lo atacan los Ground Hawgs, una pandilla de mutantes convertidos en ciclistas del Doctor Ánimo. Pero cuando los Hawgs se dan cuenta de que la falsa aldea de minigolf no es un lugar real, Ben debe transformarse en alienígena para detenerlos antes de que elijan la ciudad verdadera que está a pocos metros de allí como su blanco.

removed.title: Bringing Up Baby
removed.description: Zoe leaves Axel in charge of the school project - watching over an infant simulator doll - but when MadCap brings the doll to life, Axel and the team must stop the baby without damaging it or risk getting a failing grade!

removed.title: King Worm
removed.description: Finn has a particularly vivid dream, and all of Ooo is in it or does he?

removed.title: Would You Like to Enter Prime Empire?
removed.description: While investigating a heist, the ninja discover Prime Empire, a legendary unreleased arcade game that suddenly takes control of all other games in Ninjago.

removed.title: The Money
removed.description: The Wattersons have run out of money and are torn between being broke and selling out. Richard has lost all of the family's money. Nicole is happy for the Wattersons to appear in a Joyful Burger commercial for some much needed cash. However Gumball protests as he is convinced it's selling out. He persuades the family to stick to their principles, but they find sticking to a tiny budget even harder.

removed.title: Capullos de Rosa
removed.description: Steven recibe una visita sorpresa de algunos viejos amigos y una introducción aún más sorprendente a algunos nuevos.

removed.title: A Small Problem
removed.description: When Ben is not allowed on an attraction at a water park because he's too short, he decides to go alien to get even with the ride's attendant.

removed.title: Chaqueta De Mezclilla
removed.description: Los Osos encuentran una chaqueta de jean deslumbrante en un contenedor de basura. Es una de las cosas más fabulosas que jamás hayan visto, y parece convertir a aquel que la use en una persona extremadamente afortunada. Pero cuando los Osos discuten para ver quién queda a cargo de la chaqueta, empiezan a pensar que su bendición de denim se convirtió en una maldición.

removed.title: Elmore's Most Wanted
removed.description: Gumball's dad has been revealed as "Elmore's Most Wanted" - but when the Chief of Police tries to investigate, things do not go according to plan. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

removed.title: I Am Okino
removed.description: Inside one of the game zones, a Samurai named Okino faces a crisis of faith when he repeatedly fails to lead a series of Masters to victory, causing him to lose all hope, until some familiar ninja arrive.

removed.title: Breakup
removed.description:
Feeling left out, Adorabat wishes Mao Mao and Badgerclops would spend less time with each other and more time with her. When she gets
what she wishes for and accidentally breaks up their friendship, only the secret of their past can bring them back together.

removed.title: Yo Soy Okino
removed.description: Dentro de una de las zonas de juego, un Samurai llamado Okino se enfrenta a una crisis de fe cuando no logra que los Maestros obtengan la victoria.

removed.title: Ninjas Shhh
removed.description: Los Osos están hartos de la decadencia actual del protocolo en los cines. ¿Tú no lo estás? Tras autoproclamarse "la policía de los cines", se cuelan como ninjas para hacer callar a las personas que arruinan con sus malos modales la experiencia del ir al cine.

removed.title: Hole in 10
removed.description: While mini-golfing, Ben is attacked by the Ground Hawgs, a gang of Dr. Animo mutants turned bikers. When the Hawgs realize the faux mini-golf village isn't an actual town, Ben must go alien to stop them before they set their sights on the real city down the road.

removed.title: Fleas Help Me
removed.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang help their K9 pal, Charlie Burgers, get rid of his flea infestation.

removed.title: Thumb War
removed.description: As the other Titans engage in an all out thumb wrestling war, Starfire tries to broker peace.

removed.title: Rose Buds
removed.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

removed.title: Osos Habitantes
removed.description: Pardo, Panda y Polar no son más que tres forasteros en busca de un camino que los lleve a la adaptación... y si pueden conseguir algo de helado (o, en lo posible, yogur helado descremado) en el camino, imucho mejor! En cada episodio se muestran las desventuras cotidianas de los osos, que buscan comida, hacen todo tipo de tonterías y lidian unos con otros y con el mundo que los rodea. Sea cual sea la situación que enfrentan, está claro que ser un oso en un mundo civilizado y moderno no es tarea sencilla.

removed.title: Conduciendo A La Locura
removed.description: Cuando la Chatarra se rompe en un parque de casas rodantes, Ben descubre que se encuentran en la última etapa del Cali 10 Hundred-una carrera de autos épica todo terreno-en la que LaGrange, el piloto demente, ha regresado en busca de venganza contra aquellos que lo descalificaron hace años.

removed.title: Burrito
removed.description: Grizz likes Burritos. A lot. So much so that after a restaurant makes a Bear-Sized Burrito, Grizz can't bring himself to eat such a majestic work of art. He carries the burrito everywhere making it a new and increasingly smelly part of his life.

removed.title: Villain Time
removed.description: Ben must go alien to save the Hoover Dam from disaster, but when tough guy hero Tim Buktu swoops in to help, Ben must figure out if Tim is friend or foe.

removed.title: Another Don
removed.description: When Chata's most precious heirloom goes missing, Victor, Valentino and Isabella are on the case to find out who stole it!

removed.title: Separacion
removed.description: Adorabat siente que es dejada de lado y desea que Mao Mao y Colosal pasen menos tiempo juntos y más tiempo con ella. Pero cuando el deseo de Adorabat se hace realidad y destruye la amistad de Mao Mao y Colosal, solo el secreto de su pasado podrá volver a unirlos.

removed.title: Cast Aside the Truth
removed.description: Hawkodile breaks his arm in a careless spill and lies to his friends about the accident to keep from looking bad.

removed.title: Isla Dyer
removed.description: Cuando los ninjas relacionan la desaparición de Jay con Primer Imperio, van a la Isla Dyer para buscar respuestas del diseñador del juego, Milton Dyer.

removed.title: Escape from Family Dinner
removed.description: There's a huge water balloon fight at the creek but Craig is stuck at home for a family dinner, unless he can escape.

removed.title: Memories of Boom Boom Mountain
removed.description: Finn gets caught up in trying to make everyone happy.

removed.title: Party On
removed.description: As Zoe preps Cleo LeBall's birthday party, Axel and the team run damage control against a jealous crasher - Princess SugarSalt, who has turned the decorations and gifts into instruments of chaos!

removed.title: Last Laugh
removed.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

removed.title: Kryponite
removed.description: When Robin explains that knowing your weakness makes you a better superhero, Starfire journeys to find hers.

removed.title: Dyer Island
removed.description: When the ninja connect Jay's disappearance to Prime Empire, they set out to Dyer Island to seek answers from the game's designer, the elusive Milton Dyer.

removed.title: Jaga History
removed.description: Freed from the Astral Plane, Jaga, ghost of the ThunderCats mentor, is now free to visit the Cats' Lair. Which means he can finally tell them why Thundera, their home world, exploded. It's story time!

removed.title: Appleoni
removed.description: The wrong person is getting credit for a new dance craze.

removed.title: Adopt a Jackal
removed.description: After a battle with the Mutants, Jackalman gets confused and accidentally returns to the Cats' Lair with the Thundercats, he is the dumbest mutant. Jackalman pretends to be a Thundercat so his enemies won't catch him and the Thundercats pretend to play along because they feel bad for him!

removed.title: Te Gustaria Entrar a Primer Imperio?
removed.description: Mientras investigan un robo, los ninjas descubren Primer Imperio, un videojuego que  toma el control de todos los demás videojuegos de Ninjago.

removed.title: Escape de la Cena Familiar
removed.description: En el arroyo se disputa una enorme pelea con globos acuáticos, pero Craig está atrapado en la cena familiar, a menos que pueda escapar.
removed.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

removed.title: Story, Bored
removed.description: During a book signing at a medieval castle, Ben must stop Hex from getting his hands on a grimoire that can fuse its user with mythical beasts, creating monstrous hybrids!

removed.title: Best Best Friends
removed.description: Master Frown and Brock attend a friendship-themed competition intending to ruin it for everyone else, but soon discover their own friendship in need of repair.

removed.title: The Fly
removed.description: Apple and Onion must rid their apartment of a fly or face eviction.

removed.title: Level Thirteen
removed.description: Cyrus Borg discovers a shocking secret about Prime Empire, while the ninja battle an escaped Mechanic in their attempt to reach Level Thirteen and enter the game themselves.

removed.title: Hora De Ser Villano
removed.description: Ben debe transformarse en alienígena para evitar un desastre en la represa Hoover, pero cuando Tim Buktu, el heroico tipo rudo, se precipita para ayudar, Ben debe descubrir si Tim es su amigo...o su enemigo.

removed.title: Trouble Busters!/French Fry Wars
removed.description: Trouble Busters!: Now that the Awesome Brawlers are world famous Bakugan experts, they want to help people solve their Bakugan-related problems. When the world's quietest town is experiencing unexplained noises, the Awseome Brawlers are called in to get to the bottom of it./French Fry Wars: The Awesome Brawlers are arguing over who gets to eat the last french-fry. At first, each member makes a case for why they should to be the one to eat it. But the quarrel quickly escalates into trash talk and revealing secrets about one another. With everyone now upset, things take an unexpected turn.

removed.title: Nivel Trece
removed.description: Cyrus Borg descubre un secreto sobre Primer Imperio y  los ninjas enfrentan al Mecánico que escapó e intenta alcanzar el Nivel 13 para entrar al juego.

removed.title: Escaramuza
removed.description: When Val's favorite Escaramuza team loses a member, he convinces Xochi to join the squad. He becomes her coach and will do anything to win the big competition.

removed.title: The Kid From 3030
removed.description: The kids meet a mysterious kid from the future and try to help him complete his mission.

removed.title: River of Gold
removed.description: Apple and Onion find a mysterious book but they better read it fast before it disappears forever.

removed.title: Enemy Mime
removed.description: When the Sheriff's Dept fights a monster that copies their every move, they'll have to find a way to fight without fighting.

removed.title: Bird Boy Man
removed.description: Sumo discovers an injured roadrunner, names him Hot Sauce, and nurses him back to health. The two become inseparable pals, but Sumo learns that a wild animal can't be contained.

removed.title: Stretched Too Thin
removed.description: After a new combo-move leaves Masko permanently limp, Axel and the team must help the fallen luchador get his stretch back.

removed.title: The Possession
removed.description: Nicole has decided it's time to throw out the family's refrigerator. This doesn't go down too well with Richard, as it's his favorite possession. When it turns out the refrigerator is also a magical storage facility for childhood emotions and memories, it makes sense that Richard is having a hard time letting go.

removed.title: Max's Monster
removed.description: Grandpa Max's old Plumber partner, Phil, seeks Max's help to tame the monster within. (Introducing new Ben alien, Buzzshock; Re-introducing old Ben alien, Benvicktor.)

removed.title: The Spoon
removed.description: Gumball and Darwin are unwitting accomplices in a gas station robbery.

removed.title: Starry Eyes
removed.description: When Isabela goes missing, Victor and Valentino learn that a mysterious creature has been hiding in plain sight! V&V are on the case again!

removed.title: Diggin' A Hole
removed.description: Uncle Grandpa digs a hole.

removed.title: Azulejo
removed.description: Steven cuestiona los motivos de una misteriosa fusión que de repente se presenta en su casa.

removed.title: Superstar Rockin' Jay
removed.description: Now inside the Prime Empire game, the ninja find themselves in unfamiliar territory, ignorant of the rules of this world, as they try to find Zane and escape Unagami's army of Red Visors.

removed.title: Drive You Crazy
removed.description: After the Rust Bucket breaks down at a Mobile Home Park, Ben discovers they've stumbled on to the last leg of the Cali 10 Hundred, an epic, off-road auto race where mad driver Le Grange has returned for revenge against those that disqualified him years ago.

removed.title: Charlie
removed.description: You know that one annoying friend who just can't get the hint? That's Charlie, and he's Bigfoot. The Bears meet him when Charlie signs up on a home-sharing website to spend a weekend with the Bears. Charlie is the worst possible house guest for the Bears and nearly destroys their house.

removed.title: The Phantom Thief Comes to Call/Phantom Thief Ajit
removed.description: The Phantom Thief Comes to Call: An archeological discovery is made in Los Volmos. Exploration at the site is cut short, when a master thief and his apprentice attempt to steal the ancient Bakugan artifacts. When the Awesome Brawlers hear the news, they step in to thwart the thieves./Phantom Thief Ajit: An Ancient Bakugon artifact from an archeological discovery is placed in the Los Volmos Museum. The Awesome Brawlers are charged with guarding the artifacts from any further attempts thievery.

removed.title: The Trojan Bear
removed.description: When Axel opens a subscription gift-box he didn't even order, the team finds their ranks divided by a robotic bear - or Princess SugarSalt in disguise!

removed.title: Rio de Oro
removed.description: Manzana y Cebolla intentan terminar un cuento antes de que el libro desaparezca para siempre.

removed.title: Barbastella
removed.description: While flying with his new invention, Panthro hits it off with a new friend, Barbastella, the Queen of the Bats! Now Panthro needs help getting ready for his big date with her, because it turns out Panthro is terrified of bats! Lion-O and Cheetara are happy to help but, wow, that is a lot to unpack.

removed.title: Que Comience la Fiesta
removed.description: Mientras Zoe prepara la fiesta de cumpleaños de Cleo LeBall, Axel y el equipo controlan los daños contra una estrelladora celosa: ila princesa SugarSalt, que ha convertido las decoraciones y los regalos en instrumentos de caos!

removed.title: King Gus
removed.description: Things get out of hand when Mr. Gus fulfills a timeless legend and is deemed king of the food court.

removed.title: Toddler Titans...Yay!
removed.description: Control Freak thinks the Titans' humor is too juvenile for their time-slot, so he ages them down to a preschool show.

removed.title: Baby Caterpillar
removed.description: Unikitty takes in a radioactive caterpillar and raises it like a baby, unaware of the havoc it will wreak as a full-grown adult.

removed.title: Where the Wild Chads Are
removed.description: Chad takes Clarence out to the woods for some grizzly-man camping but Clarence is disappointed at the cushy set up; heaters, a hammock, even a portable TV. To make it a more rugged adventure, Clarence ditches Chad's wallet, cell phone and all their food but it may be too much wilderness for them to handle.

removed.title: Jean Jacket
removed.description: The Bears find a bedazzled jean jacket in a dumpster. It's just about the coolest thing they've ever seen and seems to make the wearer of the jacket extremely lucky.
